{"name":"Prism of Ambiguity","type":"misc","img":"modules/morkborg-3p/images/icons/misc/prism.png","data":{"containerSpace":1,"description":"<p>An external light source and a Presence DR10 test are needed to activate the prism. Its light may shine on up to two creatures healing d6 HP. For the next hour one of them lowers all test DRs by -2. If the test is failed they suffer d4 damage and their armor or a weapon is destroyed. You can use the prism twice per day.</p>","carryWeight":1,"equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"8TrFu59c1zX6K3pu":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.6ce2K9i7cVe9Ikb6"}},"_id":"0C6jqjKk87XZ7hf6"}
{"name":"Thorns of Comprehension","type":"misc","img":"modules/morkborg-3p/images/icons/misc/crown-of-thorns.png","data":{"containerSpace":1,"description":"<p>When worn, thorns pierce your flesh (d2 damage) and you Perceive All (-4DR to your next test and ignore the next two attacks to hit you as you weave aside). To regain the effect you must crown yourself anew. The damage steps up by one each time (d2 to d4 to d6 etc), until after a night&rsquo;s rest.</p>","carryWeight":1,"equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"8TrFu59c1zX6K3pu":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.s5wIdYpzDJlwtz2i"}},"_id":"4EIomHdGDrtWC3en"}
{"name":"Logical Prognostication","type":"scroll","img":"systems/morkborg/icons/items/scrolls/tablet-of-obscurity.png","data":{"containerSpace":1,"description":"<p>Using Pure Logic you can deduce the nature of any traps or mechanisms within 30 feet or of any Powers used within 60 feet.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Made from the clay of the Valley of the Unfortunate Undead, these Ochre Tablets are Relics of a forgotten mind-cult so rare they can be sold for 100 silver.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Each tablet counts as a normal-sized item. If a PC fumbles an attack/defense one tablet breaks. Otherwise, they follow the same usage rules as scrolls.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The coded glyphs are challenging to comprehend; PCs wielding their Power must have Presence +3 (minimum) or be a Forlorn Philosopher.</p>","carryWeight":1,"equipped":false,"price":100,"quantity":1,"scrollType":"tablet"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"8TrFu59c1zX6K3pu":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.qRC4GK6VfIsSQFbk"}},"_id":"4d4xxmqsFyHKWCMl"}
{"name":"Sash of the Stylite","type":"misc","img":"modules/morkborg-3p/images/icons/misc/sash.png","data":{"containerSpace":1,"description":"<p>The MIND controls the body! Nothing is good or bad but thinking makes it so including calories and protein. Wearing this belt means you feel no hunger and only need to drink water to regain HP when resting. Wearing it for more than d4 days causes you to collapse. It takes a day to regain its power.</p>","carryWeight":1,"equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"8TrFu59c1zX6K3pu":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.AzhdDJS1CQxhTGnB"}},"_id":"6I6NPS2jVKlza0B5"}
{"name":"Marked by Obscurity","type":"feat","img":"modules/morkborg-3p/images/tokens/forlorn-philosopher.png","data":{"description":"<p>An ever-shifting Tablet of Ochre Obscurity is tattooed on your flesh. Roll each morning which tablet it is. The tablet can only be used once per day but automatically succeeds.</p>","rollFormula":"","rollLabel":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"8TrFu59c1zX6K3pu":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.eXV8K2Em6Cnti6YE"}},"_id":"7BbBce8M7v2SCEVS"}
{"name":"Ping the Shared Subconscious","type":"scroll","img":"systems/morkborg/icons/items/scrolls/tablet-of-obscurity.png","data":{"containerSpace":1,"description":"<p>You sense the presence of living creatures within 70 feet even in adjacent rooms.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Made from the clay of the Valley of the Unfortunate Undead, these Ochre Tablets are Relics of a forgotten mind-cult so rare they can be sold for 100 silver.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Each tablet counts as a normal-sized item. If a PC fumbles an attack/defense one tablet breaks. Otherwise, they follow the same usage rules as scrolls.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The coded glyphs are challenging to comprehend; PCs wielding their Power must have Presence +3 (minimum) or be a Forlorn Philosopher.</p>","carryWeight":1,"equipped":false,"price":100,"quantity":1,"scrollType":"tablet"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"8TrFu59c1zX6K3pu":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.TuYzSe8eZGacyy7G"}},"_id":"9dNSR4DWVfJucjN4"}
{"name":"Structural Cryo-condensation (Freezing Moon)","type":"scroll","img":"systems/morkborg/icons/items/scrolls/tablet-of-obscurity.png","data":{"containerSpace":1,"description":"<p>Water freezes from the air forming a 15 foot long bridge or all water within 150 feet (unfortunately excluding that within living creatures) freezes.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Made from the clay of the Valley of the Unfortunate Undead, these Ochre Tablets are Relics of a forgotten mind-cult so rare they can be sold for 100 silver.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Each tablet counts as a normal-sized item. If a PC fumbles an attack/defense one tablet breaks. Otherwise, they follow the same usage rules as scrolls.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The coded glyphs are challenging to comprehend; PCs wielding their Power must have Presence +3 (minimum) or be a Forlorn Philosopher.</p>","carryWeight":1,"equipped":false,"price":100,"quantity":1,"scrollType":"tablet"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"8TrFu59c1zX6K3pu":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.3vfKhVNQzy8PP0s6"}},"_id":"EdCPuAFfF6A0zXuT"}
{"name":"Induced Irrelevance","type":"scroll","img":"systems/morkborg/icons/items/scrolls/tablet-of-obscurity.png","data":{"containerSpace":1,"description":"<p>This tablet&rsquo;s code literally removes a creature&rsquo;s essential meaning for d4 rounds. During which enemies will not attack it, even if it attacks them first.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Made from the clay of the Valley of the Unfortunate Undead, these Ochre Tablets are Relics of a forgotten mind-cult so rare they can be sold for 100 silver.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Each tablet counts as a normal-sized item. If a PC fumbles an attack/defense one tablet breaks. Otherwise, they follow the same usage rules as scrolls.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The coded glyphs are challenging to comprehend; PCs wielding their Power must have Presence +3 (minimum) or be a Forlorn Philosopher.</p>","carryWeight":1,"equipped":false,"price":100,"quantity":1,"scrollType":"tablet"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"8TrFu59c1zX6K3pu":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.0RzVu4HTqUndb5WC"}},"_id":"IXJc4cJ3KVaVcnhU"}
{"_id":"L9Vwzbx5o0OMdJm0","name":"Forlorn Philosopher","type":"class","img":"modules/morkborg-3p/images/tokens/forlorn-philosopher.png","data":{"abilities":"<p>Mental Focus, roll 3d6+2 Presence. Too Much Reading! Roll 3d6-2 Strength. Ruthless Inquisition: test Presence DR 14 to tear through others&rsquo; deceptions and delusions. Enough of these LIES! Roll d6 on the weapon table and d2 on the armor table. You begin with one Tablet of Ochre Obscurity and one of the following:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ol>\n<li>THORNS OF COMPREHENSION</li>\n<li>HEGELIAN OWL</li>\n<li>PRISM OF AMBIGUITY</li>\n<li>FLUTE OF TOSK</li>\n<li>BASH OF THE STYLITE</li>\n<li>MARKED BY OBSCURITY</li>\n</ol>","armorTableDie":"1d2","description":"The road an unreasoning maze, every temple soaked in blood, each destination drenched in gloom; you once thought that cold analysis might tame Fate itself, now that dream of reason has decayed to shifting madness and only the cold remains.","omenDie":"1d4","startingAgility":"3d6","startingHitPoints":"1d4","startingItems":"morkborg-3p.class-forlorn-philosopher,Ruthless Inquisition","startingPresence":"3d6+2","startingRolls":"morkborg-3p.rolls-forlorn-philosopher,Forlorn Philosopher Items,1\nmorkborg-3p.rolls-forlorn-philosopher,The Tablets of Ochre Obscurity,1\nmorkborg-3p.rolls-forlorn-philosopher,The Roots of your Dejection,1\nmorkborg-3p.rolls-forlorn-philosopher,The dejection of your Roots,1","startingSilver":"1d6*10","startingStrength":"3d6-2","startingToughness":"3d6","weaponTableDie":"1d6"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"8TrFu59c1zX6K3pu":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.KPgmjbh5vEtF9Hu8"}}}
{"name":"Total Matter Comprehension","type":"scroll","img":"systems/morkborg/icons/items/scrolls/tablet-of-obscurity.png","data":{"containerSpace":1,"description":"<p>Mends or breaks a normal-sized item, mundane or otherwise, including armor (increase/ decrease one tier) and weapons.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Made from the clay of the Valley of the Unfortunate Undead, these Ochre Tablets are Relics of a forgotten mind-cult so rare they can be sold for 100 silver.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Each tablet counts as a normal-sized item. If a PC fumbles an attack/defense one tablet breaks. Otherwise, they follow the same usage rules as scrolls.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The coded glyphs are challenging to comprehend; PCs wielding their Power must have Presence +3 (minimum) or be a Forlorn Philosopher.</p>","carryWeight":1,"equipped":false,"price":100,"quantity":1,"scrollType":"tablet"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"8TrFu59c1zX6K3pu":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.M6DrwNi5TvFEaxK3"}},"_id":"ftimDRnjNFc1hRWT"}
{"name":"Dream Theory","type":"scroll","img":"systems/morkborg/icons/items/scrolls/tablet-of-obscurity.png","data":{"containerSpace":1,"description":"<p>The target begins to doubt it is real. Attacking and defending against it is -2 DR (+2 DR for affected PCs).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Made from the clay of the Valley of the Unfortunate Undead, these Ochre Tablets are Relics of a forgotten mind-cult so rare they can be sold for 100 silver.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Each tablet counts as a normal-sized item. If a PC fumbles an attack/defense one tablet breaks. Otherwise, they follow the same usage rules as scrolls.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The coded glyphs are challenging to comprehend; PCs wielding their Power must have Presence +3 (minimum) or be a Forlorn Philosopher.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","carryWeight":1,"equipped":false,"price":100,"quantity":1,"scrollType":"tablet"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"8TrFu59c1zX6K3pu":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.MjQz9Cn20bYpdP7F"}},"_id":"rl6ceVnyejqG52sB"}
